When implementing, porting, or auditing a component from Figma (or planning a
devkit migration), read and follow the full skill at
[.claude/skills/figma-component-implementation/SKILL.md](../../.claude/skills/figma-component-implementation/SKILL.md).

It defines the phased workflow: per-component Figma audit before any code
(variant taxonomy, token extraction + verification against tokens.json,
pixel-sampling for baked asset colors), file planning, the devkit
implementation rules (Figma variables ⇄ CSS custom properties, Radix
primitives own behavior, typed props from variants, lucide-react interim
icons), stories/docs via the storybook-component-docs skill, play tests +
a11y, verification, and optional Code Connect.
